<h5>Islam on the Indian Ocean Rim</h5>
<p> A collection focused on the history of  cosmopolitanism, inter-regional connection and competing universalisms across the rimland of the Indian Ocean.  These lectures were developed as the digital textbook for the Islam on the Indian Ocean Rim course, co-taught by Tufts and LUMS University (Lahore) in 2012.  Lectures in this collection transgress the temporal thresholds used to periodize South Asian history into early modern, colonial and postcolonial eras.  Lectures also transgress spatial horizons by exposing connections between South Asia, Central Asia, Africa, the Arab world and Southeast Asia.</p>
</div>

