<h5>Bay of Bengal: Flow of Change</h5>
<p> A collection of lectures focused on the history of the eastern Indian Ocean and connections linking South and East Asia.  This corpus addresses themes relating to environmental change, population migration, intellectual and cultural exchange, and transformations of political economy in a pivotal arena for world politics.  Materials in this corpus were developed as the digital textbook for the Bay of Bengal: Flows of Change course, co-taught between Tufts and BRAC University (Dhaka) in 2014. </p>
